    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade FD3S RX-7 featuring the iconic 13B-REW rotary engine. This specimen maintains exceptional compression across all rotor faces, with the complex sequential twin-turbocharger system delivering a linear torque curve and seamless transition at 4,500 RPM. The chassis remains structurally rigid, benefiting from the original double-wishbone suspension geometry and a perfectly calibrated Torsen limited-slip differential. Every vacuum line in the 'rat's nest' has been inspected for thermal integrity, and the five-speed synchromesh transmission operates without notchiness or grind. This is a true purist's example, free of aftermarket ECU tuning or cooling system modifications, retaining its factory-engineered thermal management and aerodynamic profile.",
